                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 14th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Yellowish Oriental paper</support>
                        <extent>124 folios (ii+124+ii)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>230</height>
                              <width>158</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>175</height>
                              <width>120</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliation in Arabic numerals in pencil.</p>
                           <p>Ff. 16r, 16v are blank.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>Indeterminable.</p>
                           <p>No catchword.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>Water damage, usage stains.</p>
                           <p>First and last folios are more damaged; f. 1r is partially illegible.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
                           <p>Uniform layout.</p>
                           <p>Ruling is visible.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <summary>Persian Hebrew semi-cursive script of the 14th century. Scribe: <persName>Joseph ben Moses</persName>.
                     </summary>
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole" />
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>At the end (f. 124v), the last two lines are in golden letters and with geometrical ornaments (oxidised in most part).</p>
                        <p>Ink decoration at the beginning of sections (e.g. f. 49r).</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>F. 124v: note regarding the date of the manuscript added by a different, later hand: <quote xml:lang="he">נכתבו שנת המשת אלפים שיבעים ושמונה לברית עולם</quote>.
                     </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <p>BM in-house binding.</p>
                        <p>Title on spine: 'The Pentateuch. Persian. Brit. Mus. Oriental 5446.'</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
